column4: How did you get this? It's a test item! No wait, this was intentional -- you've discovered a secret!!
I'm not really sure who came up with this name? And why is it covered in flames? It feels like an inside joke that I just don't get...
Discovered by Prof Des Pierre, this fish uniquely hunts down other barrelcudas. This phenomenon is known as cannonballism.
It's so tiny, but I'm not really sure why it's funny? If someone could explain the joke to me, that'd be such a nice jester.
There's a theory that ancient civilizations used to raise these fish for ingestion? Just the thought of ingesting fish makes me shudder...
It cleans the bottom of our oceans which is filled to the brim with trash.
Some say this fish got it's name from its caring nature. Others will tell you that a shark is not a fish.
I have mad respect for this fish.
Hey, I'm walking here! Did I do that right? I honestly don't know where it's from, but people keeping saying it like it's funny, so I thought I'd try.
It's unique swimming style makes use of its rigid shape, making it surprisingly aerodynamic! You could say that it's thinking outside of its angled shape.
Something, something, something... at least a C+? I don't quite remember the joke.
It's just such an incredibly common and sadly average... Why would anyone want this?
Huh? What am I supposed to do with this -- put it on my roof? Somehow holding it gives me the ability to jump...
Well, now you can fish to your heart's content.
A special ticket only accepted by the most special being.
Holding it just makes you feel lighter!
Am I supposed to put this on my door handle? No, no, no that doesn't seem right...
